    "image_with_text_t6KzFw": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CcwiLn": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h3>Marlayna Pincott: Hype Chocolate Co-Founder and Local Community Mentor</h3><p>If there is one place you need to visit this holiday season, it is the <a href=\"https://hypechocolate.com/\">Hype Chocolate</a> headquarters located on 855 E. Hastings Street for all your unique chocolate needs. The co-founder of Hype Chocolate Marlayna filled us in on everything exciting that takes place at their chocolate shop, from <a href=\"https://hypechocolate.com/collections/private-parties-bookings\">chocolate workshops</a>, to local Indigenous youth mentorship programs, and much more. We were so inspired by the vision and collaborative spirit Hype Chocolate has taken on to support the local community. </p><p>Marlayna Pincott, a proud urban Indigenous woman of Quinault and Yaqui descent, with mixed European settler heritage, works on the traditional territories of the xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam), Sḵwx̱wú7mesh (Squamish), and səlilwətaɬ (Tsleil-Waututh) Nations. Deeply committed to reconnecting with her cultural roots, she is on a personal journey of healing and discovery, while mentoring others in their own reconnection to identity.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_CcwiLn"
      ],
